description: Likely from a corruption of "rowan tree", a phrase which would have been chanted in order to drive off witches, since the tree was believed to be a ward against evil.

verbs.description: rynt (no third-person singular simple present, no present participle, no simple past or past participle)

entries.meaning: (archaic, reflexive) stand off; move away (said by milkmaids to their cows after milking them)
